description: The second argument to parsePhoneNumber is an object

The return value of `.parsePhoneNumber()` is now in a more reasonable JSON format.
This change will probably not be breaking for most users, combined with the other patches we provide for this package.
There is no easy way to restore the old format, but there also shouldnâ€™t be any disadvantages to using the new format as long as all consumers of the return value are updated accordingly.
To see the new format and how to access properties without getter methods see: https://github.com/grantila/awesome-phonenumber#basic-usage.
